Yes, any obsession, and I used the word deliberately, reveals badness or
at least ill-directed and wasteful efforts, even an obsession about
something as important as raising one's child. You don't need to be a
parent to observe that either, merely an astute observer.

<QUOTE PREVIOUSPOST="
&gt; After
&gt; all, if we ignore Lazarus' (and on one occasion
&gt; Ford's) opinions and just look at the record, what do
&gt; we actually _know_ about the Johnsons?
